{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649333"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:03:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:03:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18358"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18358","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18358"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.54,0.36,0.03,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11076"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114362"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11076"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18358"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96363"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25689"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25692"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25840"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114362","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114362"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe femoral vein is the major vein leaving the lower limb.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following veins drains directly into the femoral vein?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anterior tibial vein","Great saphenous vein","Popliteal vein","Posterior tibial vein","Small saphenous vein"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe venous system of the lower limb includes several major veins that are responsible for returning blood to the heart. Understanding the connections between these veins is crucial for comprehending the venous drainage of the leg.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Egreat saphenous vein\u003C/strong\u003E is the longest vein in the body and drains directly into the femoral vein at the saphenofemoral junction, located in the groin region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epopliteal vein\u003C/strong\u003E drains into the femoral vein but only after it has passed through the adductor canal and becomes the femoral vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall saphenous vein\u003C/strong\u003E typically drains into the popliteal vein, not directly into the femoral vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior tibial vein\u003C/strong\u003E joins with the posterior tibial vein to form the popliteal vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior tibial vein\u003C/strong\u003E also contributes to the formation of the popliteal vein.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The great saphenous vein is the longest vein in the body and drains into the femoral vein.","The popliteal vein drains into the femoral vein after passing through the adductor canal.","The small saphenous vein typically drains into the popliteal vein, not directly into the femoral vein."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [